Dowitcher, Ring-billed Gull, Yellow-footed Gull (1 – one adult at Rock Hill
was probably the same bird seen here on 20 December), California Gull,
Herring Gull, Forster’s Tern, Rock Pigeon, Eurasian Collared-Dove, Inca
Dove, Common Ground-Dove, White-winged Dove (6 – at least six seen in
residential Brawley), Mourning Dove, Greater Roadrunner, Burrowing Owl,
Anna’s Hummingbird, Belted Kingfisher, Gila Woodpecker, Ladder-backed
Woodpecker, Northern Flicker, American Kestrel, Black Phoebe, Say’s Phoebe,
Vermilion Flycatcher (1 – one female at Sunbeam Lake), Loggerhead Shrike,
Common Raven, Tree Swallow, Barn Swallow, Verdin, Marsh Wren, Ruby-crowned
Kinglet, American Robin (1 – one at Sunbeam Lake), Brown Thrasher (1 – one
secretive bird near the southeast corner of El Centro was known present
